{
  "text": "TSS was measured using a digital hand-held refractometer (PR101-\u03b1, Atago, Japan). Three drops of juice from one segment were measured, and the procedure was repeated twice per fruit with nine single fruit replicates. TA of juice sacs was titrated with 0.1 N NaOH to the end point at pH 8.2. All the above methods were described in detail by Chen et al. [CITATION_1] .",
